Philip Boit and his compatriot Henry Bitok were trained in Finland in order to become competitive skiers. 
Both were former middle distance runners with no previous skiing experience. Their project was sponsored by sportswear giant Nike. 
Their winter training began in February 1996. Kenya had only one slot for the 1998 Winter Olympics in Nagano, which was taken by Philip Boit, 
